title: Lundqvist, Rangers sharp
text:
Photo: Bruce Bennett Image 1 of / 1 1 NEW YORK, NY - OCTOBER 22: Henrik Lundqvist #30 of the New York Rangers makes the third period save against the Arizona Coyotes at Madison Square Garden on October 22, 2015 in New York City. The Rangers defeated the Coyotes 4-1. (Photo by Bruce Bennett/Getty Images) ORG XMIT: 574711971 NEW YORK, NY - OCTOBER 22: Henrik Lundqvist #30 of the New York Rangers makes the third period save against the Arizona Coyotes at Madison Square Garden on October 22, 2015 in New York City. Henrik Lundqvist made 34 saves and Kevin Hayes scored the tiebreaking goal early in the third period to lift the New York Rangers to a 4-1 victory over the Arizona Coyotes on Thursday.
Chris Kreider , Keith Yandle and Rick Nash also scored goals for New York. Nash's goal was his 700th career point. Mats Zuccarello added two assists.
Klas Dahlbeck scored for Arizona. The Coyotes have lost four in a row after opening the season 3-0. Mike Smith made 24 saves for Arizona.
Devils 5, Senators 4 (SO): Lee Stempniak tied it with 32 seconds left in regulation and added the shootout winner for New Jersey. Travis Zajac , Jordin Tootoo and Adam Henrique also scored, and Cory Schneider made 35 saves to help the Devils improve to 3-3-1. Chris Neil , Mike Hoffman , Zack Smith and Mika Zibanejad scored for Ottawa. Andrew Hammond made 28 saves in his season debut.
Stars 4, Penguins 1: Jason Spezza scored his fifth goal of the season and Dallas beat Pittsburgh for its fifth straight victory. The Stars are 6-1-0 overall. Antti Niemi stopped 33 shots for his third victory of the season and fourth straight against Pittsburgh.
Predators 5, Ducks 1: Colin Wilson and Ryan Ellis each had a goal and two assists to lead Nashville. Mattias Ekholm , and Mike Ribeiro each had a goal and an assist and Eric Nystrom had the other goal for the Predators, who improved to 6-1. Pekka Rinne made 27 saves.
Wild 3, Blue Jackets 2: Thomas Vanek scored the go-ahead goal and Columbus fell to 0-8-0 in John Tortorella 's debut as head coach.
Blackhawks 3, Panthers 2: Chicago prevailed although 43-year-old Jaromir Jagr had his fifth goal of the season for Florida.
